messages.messageBody:
Those are real beauties. Karl and I were just talking the other day
about dollar bills and coins, and he was surprised when I mentioned
that lots of country has coins minted and bills printed (it rhymes!).
Then he nodded his head like "of course, I knew that" because it makes
sense, you know.

~Katherine

messages.messageBody:
I would have LOVED to have one of these, even in black and white, as a
kid. BEAUTIFUL posters with history of Greece, Rome, Byzantium by
color images of coins with the faces of the emperors.

Though they're missing half a dozen of the Byzantine emperors, they
have ALL the Romans. These are awesome:

http://ettuantiquities.com/Posters.htm


There are closeups of some of the coins (lots, because they're selling
them):

http://ettuantiquities.com/specials_thumbnails_page_1.htm

One with an elephant. One with a crocodile.

Sandra
